article.headline: George Mason 95, William & Mary 62
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) -- Folarin Campbell scored a career-high 23 points and Tony Skinn added 21 points and 10 rebounds to lead George Mason to a 95-62 win over William & Mary Saturday afternoon. Campbell, who usually plays for George Mason (10-8, 5-4) as a member of the "Green Team" unit of reserves, logged heavy minutes with the regulars by hitting all eight of his shots from the floor and a perfect 4-for-4 on 3-pointers. Skinn, one of the streakiest shooters for the Patriots, made 8 of 14 from the floor to help his team shoot 61 percent and match its season-high point total. Nathan Mann scored 15 points for William & Mary (5-13, 1-8), which has lost eight of its last nine games and all eight of its road games this season. Lamar Butler scored 18 points and combined with Skinn to score eight of George Mason's points during an 16-4 second-half run that helped turn a 45-30 halftime lead into a 26-point advantage. Jai Lewis had 11 points for the Patriots, who have now won three straight after losing three straight earlier this month. The Tribe kept the game close early before hitting just two field goals in the final eight minutes before halftime. William & Mary shot just 39 percent from the floor and connected on 4 of 24 3-pointers.
